  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "jq/ztB+3uv/jiDp6oCzksqlG70E=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Four architecture options lay out the full trade-space:\n\n**A \u2014 Connect + Switchboard (current default)**\n- PGlite <-> Switchboard (PostgreSQL) via GraphQL SyncManager\n- Duplication: 2x\n- Recovery: from Switchboard\n- Requires: running a server\n\n**B \u2014 Connect + Swarm plugin (no Switchboard)**\n- PGlite -> Swarm via plugin\n- Duplication: 2x\n- Recovery: from Swarm (wallet signature)\n- Requires: running a Bee node (local or remote)\n\n**C \u2014 Connect + Switchboard + Swarm (both)**\n- Both sync paths active\n- Duplication: 3x\n- Recovery: from either Switchboard OR Swarm\n- Requires: server + Bee node\n\n**D \u2014 Connect on Swarm (fully decentralized, end goal)**\n- Connect SPA deployed to Swarm via ENS\n- PGlite <-> Swarm via plugin (no Switchboard)\n- Collaboration: SwarmChannel (peer-to-peer via feeds)\n- Duplication: 2x (same as B and A)\n- Recovery: from Swarm (wallet signature)\n- Requires: wallet + local Bee node\n- Servers: ZERO\n\n**Key insight**: the end-goal architecture (D) has **identical 2x duplication** to the current default (A). Going fully decentralized does not cost extra storage \u2014 it just swaps where the remote copy lives (server PostgreSQL -> Swarm network).",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
    }
  },
